					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A kabbalistic treatise by Aaron Berechiah ben Moses of Modena.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="211v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Shemen mishḥat ḳodesh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שמן משחת קדש</title>
							<note>
								<p>The manuscript consists of several works by Gure ha-Ari: a derush of Shimshon Bek (sent from Jerusalem to Italy in 1585); an abridgment of derushim of Joseph ibn Tabul; Limude atsilut of Israel Saruk; Ma'amar of Menachem Azariah da Fano; parts of Liḳutim ascribed to Israel Saruk and Menachem Azariah da Fano; derushim of Hayim Vital; Hatḥalat ha-ḥokhmah and various notes and comments by the students of Ari.</p>
								<p>According to the introduction, the work was composed in 1629: ס' שמן משחת קדש יהיה זה לי אב"מ. לדורו' עולם )אהרון ברכיה מודינה = אב"מ). </p>
								<p>See also <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">545-547</ref>, volume 2; Tishby, <ref target="Tsiyon" type="number">39</ref> (1974), pp. 15, 63-70.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90404354">Aaron Berechiah ben Moses, of Modena, 1549-1639</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90404354">מודנה, אהרן ברכיה בן משה</persName>
							</author>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">חלק א' מכללי והקדמות חכמת הקבלה מגורי האר"י זצ"ל.<locus n="2r"/>
							</incipit>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
